      • ZooKeeperReplicationConfig

        public ZooKeeperReplicationConfig​(String connectionString,
                                  String pathPrefix,
                                  int timeoutMillis,
                                  int numWorkers,
                                  int maxLogCount,
                                  long minLogAgeMillis)
        Creates a new replication configuration.
        Parameters:
        connectionString - the ZooKeeper connection string. e.g. "zk1.example.com:2181,zk2.example.com:2181,zk3.example.com:2181"
        pathPrefix - the ZooKeeper path prefix. e.g. "/service/dogma"
        timeoutMillis - the ZooKeeper timeout, in milliseconds
        numWorkers - the number of worker threads dedicated for replication
        maxLogCount - the maximum number of log items to keep in ZooKeeper. Note that the log items will still not be removed if they are younger than minLogAgeMillis.
        minLogAgeMillis - the minimum allowed age of log items before they are removed from ZooKeeper

        public int timeoutMillis()
        Returns the ZooKeeper timeout, in milliseconds. If unspecified, the default of 1000 is returned.

      • numWorkers

        public int numWorkers()
        Returns the number of worker threads dedicated for replication. If unspecified, the default of 16 is returned.

      • maxLogCount

        public int maxLogCount()
        Returns the maximum number of log items to keep in ZooKeeper. Note that the log items will still not be removed if they are younger than minLogAgeMillis(). If unspecified, the default of 100 is returned.

      • minLogAgeMillis

        public long minLogAgeMillis()
        Returns the minimum allowed age of log items before they are removed from ZooKeeper. If unspecified, the default of 1 hour is returned.
